sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Init as total-recall init
    participant Prompt as Huh TUI prompts
    participant UserCfg as ~/.tr/config.yaml
    participant RepoCfg as .tr.yaml
    participant Installer as internal/hooks.Installer
    participant GitHooks as .git/hooks/*
    participant Serve as total-recall serve
    participant Config as internal/config
    participant Daemon as localhost:7331
    participant Status as total-recall status
    participant Git as git
    participant Hook as managed hook script

    User->>Init: Run inside a Git repository
    Init->>UserCfg: Load existing config or default values
    Init->>Prompt: Ask for conversation analysis opt-in
    Prompt-->>Init: true / false
    Init->>UserCfg: WriteUserConfig()
    Init->>RepoCfg: Load existing repo config
    Init->>Prompt: Ask which hooks to enable
    Prompt-->>Init: pre-commit / commit-msg / pre-push selections
    Init->>RepoCfg: WriteRepoConfig()
    Init->>Installer: InstallEnabled(hooks)
    Installer->>GitHooks: Create or regenerate managed hooks
    Installer-->>User: Print config + hook install summary

    User->>Serve: Start daemon
    Serve->>Config: Load(quiet)
    Config-->>Serve: Resolved merged config
    Serve->>Daemon: Start HTTP server on localhost:7331
    Daemon-->>User: Daemon running

    User->>Status: Check status
    Status->>Daemon: GET /health
    Daemon-->>Status: {"status":"ok"}
    Status->>Config: Load(quiet)
    Config-->>Status: Resolved config with sources
    Status-->>User: Running + config summary

    loop Regular hook-driven usage
        User->>Git: git commit / git push
        Git->>Hook: Run enabled managed hook
        Hook->>Hook: Gather envelope fields + hook payload
        alt Daemon reachable
            Hook->>Daemon: POST /hooks/pre-commit|commit-msg|pre-push
            Daemon-->>Hook: 202 {"status":"received"}
            Hook-->>Git: Exit 0
            Git-->>User: Operation continues
        else Daemon unavailable
            Hook-->>User: Print advisory to start total-recall serve
            Hook-->>Git: Exit 0
            Git-->>User: Operation continues
        end
    end

    Note over Daemon: Current runtime logs hook metadata and returns accepted.\nRecall synthesis, cache writes, and MCP tools are reserved for later phases.
